oth rally and drive teams and effectively operate within a rapidly growing organization Demonstrated ability to drive execution in complex environments Demonstrated fit with HealthVerity\u2019s culture and values Demonstrated technical proficiency and effectiveness working closely with engineers Excellent financial modeling skills, for both cost and revenue Self-starter with high levels of initiative, commitment and energy who can galvanize the team to follow Preferred Experience Experience with Life Sciences and/or Payer enterprises or in a regulated industry such as financial services or government Consulting experience with firms such as PWC, BCG, McKinsey Startup experience, including working closely with founders or a founding team Experience defining product requirements in one of the following problem domains: Software as a Service (SaaS), Platform as a Service (PaaS), hosted applications or services delivered through APIs Experience with blockchain technologies such as Hyperledger HealthVerity, based in Center City Philadelphia, is a venture-backed technology company that is transforming the way data-led organizations make critical decisions. Our technology platform serves as the foundation for the rapid creation, exchange and management of healthcare and consumer data in a fully-interoperable, privacy-protecting manner. Advantaged by highly sophisticated identity resolution and matching capabilities, HealthVerity is on a mission to increase transparency, forge interoperability and activate deeper insights. Our company challenges Empowering clients with highly rewarding data discovery and licensing tools Ingesting and managing billions of healthcare records from a wide variety of partners Standardizing on common data models across data types Orchestrating an industry-leading HIPAA privacy layer Innovating our proprietary de-identification and data science algorithms Building a culture that supports rapid iteration and new possibilities The infrastructure and culture we are building will provide an environment that cultivates innovation. We want to move fast knowing we can fix anything we break along the way. If a new need arises, we want to turn around a solution quickly. We want to solve our challenges in ways that create even more possibilities. We\u2019re creating a platform that lets us discover what else we might do. HealthVerity is an equal opportunity employer. ", 
